x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Zeitschrift fuer Physik A, Hadrons and Nuclei, Vol.342, p.471 (1992)

x4freetext: 7-Li(P,A)4-He have Been Studied Over the C.M.  Energy
Range E=10 to 1450 KeV.  Each Reaction Involved the Use
Of Hydrogen Projectiles and Lif Solid Targets As Well
As Li Projectiles and Hydrogen Molecular Gas Targets.
In All Cases the Effects of Electron Screening on the
ENHANCEMENT) Have Been Observed;  the Effects are
Somewhat Stronger in the Case of Atomic P or D
Projectiles Compared to the Case of Molecular H2 or
D2 Gas Targets.  If Isotopic Effects on Electron
Screening are Negligible, All Three Reactions Should
Exhibit the Same Enhancements For Each Set of
This Expectation to a Large Extent.
KV, AND 4 MV) Provided P, D,6-Li, and 7-Li Ion Beams in
The C.M.  Energy Range E = 10 to 1450 KeV.  At the
Lowest Energies, the P and D Beam Currents on Target
Were 600 Mu-A and Those of the 6-Li and 7-Li Beams were
40 Mu-A.  At Higher Energies the Currents were  Limited
By Dead Time Effects in the Detectors (KEPT BELOW 3%)
Or by Requirements of the Beam Calorimeters.  The
Absolute Ion Beam Energy of the Accelerators is Known
To Sufficient Precision and has Been Tested For the 350
And 400 Kv Accelerators During the Course of the
1.0   KeV For 400 KeV and 4. MeV Accelerators.
